../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:9:This chain has real upside. If a genuinely exact small helical/Fourier subsystem existed that stayed phase-locked long enough to realize Tao-like delayed transfer under honest conjugate and spectator accounting, the firewall would indeed be in serious trouble quickly.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:15:- phase locking should be discoverable by a manageable parameter search;
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:23:- "Smallest honest support family" is undefined. Smallest by mode count, shell count, active triads, parameter dimension, or closure depth? Without a strict ordering, Step 1 can be gamed indefinitely.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:24:- The chain confuses decisive positive evidence with informative negative evidence. A positive exact construction would kill the firewall. A negative search over a handcrafted family does not support the firewall much unless the search space is proved exhaustive.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:25:- It pushes honesty checks too late. Spectator channels, closure cascades, and robustness are treated as downstream tests, but they should constrain the candidate family from the start.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:27:- It risks prior-art redundancy. Small helical triad or triad-cluster searches are an obvious place to look. Unless the chain can show exact closure, delayed transfer, and spectator suppression all at once, it may just rediscover toy-model behavior that nobody would count as a firewall kill.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:28:- Its kill conditions are mostly qualitative. Phrases like "meaningful phase-locking ansatz," "ordinary cascade behavior," and "meaningful delayed transfer event" are too elastic for a search procedure that is already parameter-rich.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:32:### Step 1 - Freeze the smallest honest support family
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:34:- The strong part is the insistence on conjugate completion, Leray projection, and companion modes. That is the right honesty instinct.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:35:- The weak part is that "include any companion triads that appear immediately" is not enough. Exact closure is recursive, not first-generation. A newly forced companion mode can generate further forcing on the next interaction. If the closure criterion is only "immediate spillover," hidden leakage is being smuggled in from the first step.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:37:- The step assumes Tao's five roles should already guide support selection. That is a major overfit. It prejudges the mechanism before the exact NS algebra has spoken.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:38:- The parameter list is too open-ended to be a serious first step: triad shape, helicity signs, scale ratio, amplitude hierarchy. That is a broad search space with no pruning logic. "Smallest" plus "search over many knobs" is not a disciplined combination.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:39:- The Step 1 kill condition is overclaimed. Showing that one notion of finite honest support spills over immediately would only kill this minimal exact-subsystem route, not the broader possibility that the firewall fails in a larger exact network.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:41:### Step 2 - Derive the exact reduced dynamics and candidate locking manifolds
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:43:- This step only makes sense if Step 1 has already proved genuine invariance of the chosen support. If not, the "exact projected ODEs" are not exact reduced dynamics; they are truncated dynamics.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:44:- "Candidate constant-phase or slowly drifting phase manifolds" is too permissive. If constant locking fails, the chain can always retreat to "slow drift" and keep the story alive. That is bad kill-discipline.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:46:- "Mark which phase relations correspond to the desired transfer directions" still sneaks in desired-channel bias. The mission is supposed to avoid hand-chosen channel narratives where possible.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:47:- There is no requirement to distinguish a true invariant or normally hyperbolic locking manifold from a coordinate artifact or a transiently favorable phase relation along one orbit.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:53:- It is not clear that the claimed knobs are really independent. In exact triad geometry, scale ratios and admissible shapes are constrained by the triad relation. Helicity choices also constrain coefficient signs and strengths. The chain talks like it has more free design freedom than exact NS may actually allow.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:54:- "Ordinary cascade behavior" is not a calibrated failure condition. You need a quantitative threshold for delayed-transfer behavior relative to turnover time, viscous decay time, or another intrinsic clock. Otherwise almost any transient can be narrated either way.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:57:### Step 4 - Test stability of the locking window against spectators and viscosity
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:59:- Spectators are being treated too late. If they matter enough to kill the window, they matter enough to belong in the exact support audit from Step 1 onward. Deferring them to Step 4 makes the earlier subsystem look cleaner than it really is.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:60:- "Measure how long the phase-locking manifold or near-manifold persists" sounds numerical and trajectory-specific. That is weak evidence unless the chain states a robustness standard: open set of initial data, codimension-one tuning, or exact invariant family.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:62:- The step asks whether spectator channels stay subordinate during the window, but does not define a subordinate threshold. If the firewall is about delayed transfer surviving honest spectator burden, that threshold should have been explicit much earlier.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:63:- A short-lived near-locking episode that barely survives long enough for one favorable transfer event is probably not enough to "kill the firewall." The chain blurs the line between transient coincidence and reusable mechanism.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:69:- A negative outcome is much less informative than the step implies. If the chosen subsystem fails because of coefficient rigidity or spectator blowup, that may be a defect of the chosen minimal family, not a firewall-level obstruction.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:70:- The handoff menu is too coarse. "Coefficient rigidity" or "no honest delayed window" is not yet reusable unless the chain has proved that the obstruction survives changes of support size, geometry class, or role assignment.
../../../../missions/exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:71:- This step inherits the earlier lack of quantitative standards. "Sustained phase coherence long enough" still has no intrinsic metric, so the final comparison remains vulnerable to narrative drift.
