+Question:
+
+For mission `exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall`, step `step-001`, identify the
+strongest local repository materials for freezing the Step-1 intrinsic object,
+equivalence/admissibility test, exact search class, and quantitative metrics
+for the chain
+`Intrinsic Exact Closed-Support Delayed-Transfer Stress Test`.
+
+Return concrete findings, not just file paths, on these exact questions:
+
+1. Which local materials best support a very small family of candidate exact
+   phase/coherence objects built directly from exact Fourier or helical
+   interaction data, without desired-channel labels, packet sheets, or frozen
+   transfer annotations in the raw definition?
+2. Among locally supported candidates, which ones look most plausible as:
+   `intrinsic`,
+   `canonically representable but non-intrinsic`,
+   or
+   `inadmissible`,
+   once the following equivalences are tested explicitly:
+   conjugation,
+   real-valued conjugate completion,
+   helical-sign relabeling,
+   phase gauge conventions,
+   normalization changes,
+   and representation changes?
+3. Which local materials best justify a canonical exact search object and
+   support class for this branch, including:
+   finite Fourier support vs finite helical support,
+   closure under recursive triad forcing,
+   spectator inclusion,
+   admissible enlargements,
+   smallest-first ordering,
+   and an escalation ladder?
+4. Which local materials best support quantitative delayed-transfer-facing
+   metrics tied to intrinsic clocks rather than narrative language, including:
+   transfer delay relative to turnover time,
+   transfer delay relative to viscous time,
+   spectator burden during the same window,
+   and a robustness standard?
+5. Does the inherited local record already force any negative conclusion:
+   no intrinsic candidate survives,
+   no canonical search class is honest,
+   or no quantitative metric sheet can be stated sharply enough?
+   If so, what exact blocker is locally earned?
+6. What is the minimum honest exploration split for Step 1:
+   one intrinsicity screen,
+   one search-class freeze,
+   and one metrics/readiness exploration,
+   or can any of these be collapsed without losing clarity?
+7. Which exact local files would later let Step 1 cite:
+   mission-context claims,
+   the admissibility status of each candidate,
+   the canonical support policy,
+   the closure/escalation rules,
+   the delayed-transfer metric sheet,
+   and the final Step-2-readiness verdict?
+
