+# Exploration 003 Summary
+
+## Goal
+
+Define quantitative delayed-transfer metrics for the
+`exact-ns-phase-locking-firewall`
+branch using the intrinsic-object and search-class freezes, and issue a clean
+verdict on whether Chain Step 2 is now well-posed.
+
+## What I Tried
+
+- Read the mission/chain brief and the attack / judgment material that demanded
+  turnover-time, viscous-time, spectator-burden, and robustness thresholds.
+- Used the finished Exploration 001 and 002 freezes as inputs rather than
+  reopening object or support semantics.
+- Translated the branch's later success test into exact closed-support energy
+  inflow observables and fixed one event threshold, one burden threshold, and
+  one robustness rule.
+
+## Outcome
+
+`succeeded`
+
+## One Key Takeaway
+
+Step 2 is now well-posed: later steps must score delayed transfer by the exact
+cumulative nonlinear inflow `J_B`, require the event to wait at least
+`3 tau_turn` but arrive before `tau_nu / 4`, enforce spectator burden
+`J_R <= J_B / 4`, and refuse to count a single tuned trajectory as success.
+
+## Leads Worth Pursuing
+
+- Step 2 can now enumerate the first-budget closed supports without inventing
+  new metrics later.
+- Step 3 can instantiate the `A / B / R` partition only after the support and
+  exact dynamics are frozen, while still using the already-frozen formulas.
+- Step 4 can now kill ordinary fast transfer, viscously irrelevant transients,
+  and spectator-dominated episodes without narrative drift.
+
+## Unexpected Findings
+
+- The cleanest exact transfer observable was not a triad-by-triad signed sum
+  but the closed-support energy-balance quantity `J_X`, because it removes
+  viscous loss without importing desired-channel bookkeeping.
+- The metrics become sharp only after separating the intrinsic object from the
+  later transfer partition: Step 1 can freeze the formulas even though the
+  eventual `A / B / R` split is chosen later on a fixed support.
+
+## Computations Worth Doing Later
+
+- Evaluate `tau_turn`, `tau_nu`, `J_B`, and `J_R` on the first genuinely closed
+  supports that survive Step 2.
+- Test whether any Step-3 compatible phase regime satisfies the delayed-event
+  and spectator-burden inequalities on an open reduced regime rather than on a
+  single orbit.
