 # History of Report Summaries
 
 Exploration summaries will be appended here as they land.
+
+## Exploration 001 Summary
+
+- Goal:
+  identify a very small candidate family of exact phase/coherence objects built
+  from exact Fourier or helical interaction data and classify each candidate
+  under an explicit equivalence/admissibility test.
+- Outcome:
+  `succeeded`.
+- Takeaway:
+  `[INFERRED]` the best surviving intrinsic object is the coefficient-corrected
+  exact triad-phase orbit measure `Mu_S(a)`;
+  scalar coherence summaries are only canonical diagnostics;
+  any desired-vs-spectator phase split is definitionally inadmissible because
+  it imports the target transfer route by hand.
+
+## Exploration 002 Summary
+
+- Goal:
+  freeze the exact search object and support class for Chain Step 2, together
+  with recursive closure, spectator inclusion, admissible enlargements,
+  smallest-first ordering, and escalation ladder.
+- Outcome:
+  `succeeded`.
+- Takeaway:
+  `[INFERRED]` Step 2 should enumerate finite helical mode supports with
+  mandatory conjugate completion and recursive exact closure;
+  packet families may still be used as seed templates, but not as the primary
+  search object;
+  every closure-forced spectator mode belongs in the exact support ledger from
+  the start.
+
+## Exploration 003 Summary
+
+- Goal:
+  define quantitative delayed-transfer metrics using the intrinsic-object and
+  search-class freezes, and issue a clean verdict on whether Chain Step 2 is
+  well-posed.
+- Outcome:
+  `succeeded`.
+- Takeaway:
+  `[INFERRED]` Step 2 is now well-posed:
+  later steps must score delayed transfer by the exact cumulative inflow
+  `J_B`,
+  require the event to wait at least `3 tau_turn` but arrive before
+  `tau_nu / 4`,
+  enforce spectator burden
+  `J_R <= J_B / 4`,
+  and refuse to count a single tuned trajectory as success.
